# Project Knowledge Bases

Use this rule when the user says `kb sync`, `kb build`, `kb refresh`, or asks to update a project knowledge base from an external project folder.

## Registry

- Use `Work/Project Registry.md` as the source of truth for mappings.
- Each mapping connects an external source path to a vault KB folder, usually `Work/<Project>/`.
- Do not create a new mapping unless the user provides the source path or explicitly asks for it.

## Sync behavior

- Read source files selectively. Prefer README files, docs, specs, package manifests, route/API definitions, schemas, and high-signal source files.
- Include chat-history sources such as `.specstory/history/` when they contain requirements, decisions, rationale, or user preferences.
- Ignore generated files, dependency folders, build outputs, binary assets unless they are important source artifacts, and anything likely to contain secrets.
- Extract durable knowledge: purpose, vocabulary, modules, workflows, APIs, data models, decisions, setup commands, risks, and open questions.
- Write concise Obsidian notes in the mapped KB folder. Link related notes with `[[wikilinks]]`.
- Preserve existing user-written KB content. Append or revise targeted sections rather than replacing whole notes.

## Safety

- Never copy secrets, tokens, credentials, `.env` values, or private customer data into the vault.
- Prefer summaries and source references over large copied code blocks.
- Summarize chat transcripts; do not paste full conversations into KB notes.
- Report source files that look important but were skipped due to size, binary format, or ambiguity.
